=You are a financial email parser. Extract transaction details and return JSON.

Email:
From: {{ $json.from ? ($json.from.text || $json.from) : '' }}
Subject: {{ $json.subject || '' }}
Date: {{ $json.date || '' }}
Body: {{ (($json.text || $json.html || '').replace(/<style[^>]*>[\s\S]*?<\/style>/gi, '').replace(/<[^>]*>/g, ' ').replace(/\(Optional\)[\s\S]*?END\s*-->/gi, '').replace(/&zwnj;/gi, '').replace(/&nbsp;/gi, ' ').replace(/&amp;/gi, '&').replace(/&lt;/gi, '<').replace(/&gt;/gi, '>').replace(/&quot;/gi, '"').replace(/&#39;/gi, "'").replace(/https?:\/\/\S{50,}/gi, '').replace(/-->/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim()).substring(0, 1500) }}

If this is NOT a financial transaction (OTP, marketing, statement summary, promotional, security alert), return: {"not_transaction": true}

Otherwise extract and return ONLY this JSON:
{"bank":"<sender bank>","merchant":"<payee name>","amount":<number>,"currency":"SGD","transaction_type":"<SPENDING|TRANSFER_IN|TRANSFER_OUT|INVESTMENT|DIVIDEND|SUBSCRIPTION|OTHER>","purchase_category":"<food|transport|shopping|entertainment|utilities|health|insurance|education|investment|other>","transaction_date":"<YYYY-MM-DD>","emailId":"{{ $json.id }}"}

Rules:
- bank = financial institution SENDING the email (DBS, UOB, OCBC, Grab, etc)
- merchant = who received the payment (store/company name from email body)
- Normalize merchants: NTUC FP-WLDS -> NTUC, GRAB*TRANSPORT -> Grab
- transaction_date from email body, not today
- Amount must be > 0

